- The Greatest Hits appears focused on polished, melodic mid‑tempo tracks rather than the energetic, radio‑friendly, glossy mid‑1980s production traits (bright midrange, rhythmic clarity and punchy, hook‑driven arrangements) I favor. It may be great for vocal‑forward listening, but it is less aligned with my priority for dense, energetic full‑band AOR anthologies and the immersive three‑disc sequencing implied by The Platinum Collection.
Conclusion: The Platinum Collection better satisfies my core preferences for a detailed, career‑spanning anthology with preserved dynamics, precise imaging and coherent sequencing that support the dense, punchy, start‑to‑finish AOR listening experience I value, while the Greatest Hits leans toward warmer, vocal‑forward and mid‑tempo treatments that conflict with my dislike of overly mellow/acoustic‑forward mixes.

